title: For Sale:  British Enfield Trials No.1 Mk.5
postcontent: Up for sale is a very rare British Enfield No1 MkV. It has a production number of only 20,000 ever made, with majority unaccounted for.  These never were officially assigned to any units and many did not get the rear sight apperature completed as rumored.  Some photos have popped up with these rifles in the hands of rebel fighters, fueling the theory that they were given to the foreign units because they were of no use to England etc.  There is another rumor that these were used heavily during the Dunkirk battle and many lost...  None the less, this is a rare rifle.  The good is that the barrel is uncut and the rifling is in great shape.  Markings are clear etc.  Also has "V" designation on small parts that would otherwise be impossible to find.  The bad is that the stock has been cut, rear sights absent, and lug holes to the rear sight are missing.  With a little work this can be a nice piece of history brought back.  Go onto a forum and these go for up to $2600, and are highly sought after.  Parts are remanufactured by a British company named EFD?  I will include some rear sights from a Pattern 17 rifle that can be fabricated.  Also a magazine cutoff has been reinstalled onto the rifle.   $250 OBO
